From f58d9c1cd175f4c6ce653b7d5fce371b77bdc20c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ASK2 PR14h <ask2@vyos-ls1046a-build>
Date: Sat, 16 May 2026 05:22:51 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fman: PCD: add Offline-Host (OH) port driver

Implements the public OH-port ABI per ASK2 spec v1.2 section 13.3 and
LS1046A RM 8.11.  The OH port is the silicon mechanism that lets a
classified frame be re-injected into a second-pass classify/manipulate
chain and then re-enqueued to a peer port's TX FQ - all without the
A72 cores touching the frame.  This is the only LS1046A mechanism by
which L3-routed forwarding with per-hop L2 rewrite can be offloaded.

Public ABI (EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL, consumed by ask.ko in PR14j):

  fman_pcd_oh_port_claim(struct fman *, u8 oh_idx)
  fman_pcd_oh_port_release(struct fman_pcd_oh_port *)
  fman_pcd_oh_port_input_fqid(const struct fman_pcd_oh_port *)
  fman_pcd_oh_port_set_chain(struct fman_pcd_oh_port *,
                             struct fman_pcd_manip * const *manips,
                             u8 n_manips, u32 sink_fqid)

Wiring:
 - fman_port.c learns the 'fsl,fman-v3-port-oh' compatible so the
   six upstream-defined OH platform nodes at 0x82000..0x87000 in
   qoriq-fman3-0.dtsi (cell-index 0x2..0x7) get a platform_device.
 - fman_pcd.c gains a pcd->oh_ports list_head and a teardown-time
   fman_pcd_oh_reclaim_all() sweep that drains leaked handles.
 - fman_pcd_internal.h exports fman_pcd_get_oh_list() so
   fman_pcd_oh.c can access the list under pcd->lock.
 - Makefile builds fman_pcd_oh.o into fsl_dpaa_fman when
   CONFIG_FSL_FMAN_PCD=y.

PR14h skeleton publishes a 'null walker' AD chain (all-zero 16-byte
entries) regardless of the manip argument - the per-AD encoder lands
in a follow-up PR after PR14i adds the RMV_ETHERNET / INSRT_GENERIC /
FIELD_UPDATE_IPV4_FORWARD manip types that it consumes.  The skeleton
still validates the chain arguments (n_manips<=4, non-NULL manip
pointers, 24-bit sink_fqid) and records n_manips + sink_fqid on the
handle so PR14j ask.ko code can be authored against a stable ABI.

Builds clean on aarch64 (linux-6.18.29) with both CONFIG_FSL_FMAN=y
and CONFIG_FSL_FMAN_PCD=y.  All four __ksymtab_fman_pcd_oh_* symbols
appear in vmlinux.
